<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-74-0269 </DOCNO><TEXT>This report presents the results of a survey of US nuclear power plantsconducted in the spring of 1987; the survey focused on the status of45 `generic' information systems relevant to the business of operatinga nuclear power plant. The report provides a detailed analysis for 50%of the nuclear plants in the United States. The report is organized accordingto six major ``families'' of systems: operations and maintenance informationsystems; nuclear plant engineering information systems; plant materialsmanagement information systems; personnel related systems; financialrelated systems; and administrative support systems.</TEXT></DOC>